mily and I ate at Px Mediterranean Grill last week in Fort Lauderdale, Florida.\\n\\nThey specialize in Kosher Foods and the flavors were out of this world \\ud83c\\udf0d good \\ud83d\\udcab\\n\\nWe started w the Arais $17.95 (Ground Beef Kabob Grilled to perfection in a Pita \\ud83e\\uded3 Pocket) That is what the menu stated, and it was true, it was absolutely grilled to perfection!!!! The flavors were on point and this might have been my favorite flavor of the night.\\n\\nWe ordered the Fried Combo $19.95 (Pastel 3 Pcs, Cigar 3 Pcs, Kibbeh 3pc)  I absolutely love fried things so we had to try the combo. You could tell they use fresh oil because there was no taste of old fry oil, I really appreciate that. The textures were spot on, and I enjoyed all three selections.\\n\\nI ordered the Schnitzel Plate 2 Pcs. $31.95 and it came w fries. This dish was really good and executed well. It also came w rice and this stews okra w tomato sauce on top. It was very good and added a great complement of acidity to the dish.\\n\\nThey also brought complimentary side items to go w the meal that was really good. Seriously, all the flavors were on point \\ud83d\\udcab\\n\\nMy wife order the Greek Salad With Vegan Feta $17.95 It was good. I asked the waiter why vegan feta and he said because they were Kosher. I thought that was cool \\ud83d\\ude0e\\n\\nFor dessert we ordered a Peanut Butter Dome $12.95 & a Chocolate Dome $12.95 The presentation was fabulous! They were decadent, rich and over the top. Everything a dessert should be \\ud83d\\ude09 I am a huge peanut butter fan and always have to order if I see a dessert w it. So so glad we did!\\n\\nPX Mediterranean Grill\\n3558 N Ocean Blvd,\\nFort Lauderdale, FL 33308\\n\\nThe Chefs View", "time": 1685071460, "translated": false}, {"author_name": "Donna Segal", "author_url": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106597380856163358592/reviews", "language": "en", "original_language": "en", "profile_photo_url": "https://lh3.googleuserco